images.name: Kyler Murray  [600x400]
images.caption: QB Kyler Murray, summing up Sunday's loss to the Titans -- a game the Cardinals led 21-3: "That was bad. That was bad. Bad. All around, it was bad."

articles.description: QB Kyler Murray didn't know what to think after the Cardinals' 22-21 defeat to the lowly Titans -- a game Arizona led 21-3 but was ultimately derailed by two botched plays in the fourth quarter.
articles.headline: 'Bonehead mistakes' derail Cardinals in loss to lowly Titans

images.name: LEDE: Tyran Stokes [608x342]
images.alt: Tyran Stokes of Team USA poses for a portrait
images.caption: The 6-7, 230-pound Notre Dame (CA) star scored in his football debut before taking the hardwood in the Border League at 9 p.m. ET on ESPN2.

articles.description: The 6-7, 230-pound Notre Dame (CA) star scored in his football debut before taking the hardwood in the Border League at 9 p.m. ET on ESPN2.
articles.headline: Tyran Stokes aims to join LeBron, Iverson and more as a two-sport star

articles.description: Buccaneers WR Emeka Egbuka continued his dazzling rookie campaign Sunday, collecting 163 receiving yards, a touchdown and a 2-point conversion in a 38-35 victory over the Seahawks in Seattle.
articles.headline: Bucs hail 'outstanding' Emeka Egbuka after latest late win

images.name: Cam Ward [600x400]
images.caption: The win by Tennessee -- Cam Ward's first in the NFL -- snapped a 10-game losing streak dating back to last season.

articles.description: It took five tries, but Titans rookie quarterback Cam Ward finally got his first NFL win behind an improbable fourth-quarter comeback Sunday at Arizona.
articles.headline: QB Cam Ward earns first NFL win as Titans stun Cardinals

articles.description: Week 5 action started off with Minnesota's win against Cleveland Sunday morning in London. Follow the highlights here.
articles.headline: Week 5 NFL highlights: Best plays, moments and touchdowns

articles.description: Washington Commanders quarterback Jayden Daniels returned from injury, and playing for the first time near his hometown of San Bernardino, he helped orchestrate his club's 27-10 victory over the Los Angeles Chargers on Sunday afternoon at SoFi Stadium.
articles.headline: Jayden Daniels returns, sparks rally in Commanders' victory
